 fundamentally deficient. In an appendix we show that\nthe number-density distribution function, to be distinguished from the\nsite-occupation distribution function, corresponding to the GS of the Hubbard\nHamiltonian is not non-interacting v-representable, a fact established earlier\nnumerically. [Abridged Abstract]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 9 May 2013 13:46:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-05-10"}
